# 🧠 Important Patterns Learned

## Stack

- Monotonic Increasing Stack
- Monotonic Decreasing Stack
- Expression Parsing
- Previous / Next Greater Element
- Previous / Next Smaller Element
- Stack Simulation
- Index Based Stack
- Contribution Technique

---

## Queue

- FIFO
- Circular Queue
- Deque
- Sliding Window

---

## Monotonic Stack Pattern

Used whenever the problem asks for:

- Next Greater Element
- Next Smaller Element
- Previous Greater Element
- Previous Smaller Element
- First Greater/Smaller Element
- Contribution Technique

---

## Contribution Technique

Instead of generating every subarray:

```text
Contribution =
Element × Left Choices × Right Choices
```

Used in:

- Sum of Subarray Minimums
- Sum of Subarray Maximums
- Sum of Subarray Ranges

---

## Histogram Pattern

```text
Binary Matrix
        ↓
Convert each row into Histogram
        ↓
Largest Rectangle in Histogram
```

Used in:

- Largest Rectangle in Histogram
- Maximal Rectangle

---

## Sliding Window Pattern

```text
Moving Window
        ↓
Maintain Useful Elements
        ↓
Deque
```

Used in:

- Sliding Window Maximum

---

## Stack Simulation Pattern

Used when elements interact with previously processed elements.

Examples:

- Asteroid Collision
- Balanced Parentheses
- Remove K Digits
- Min Stack

---

## Index Based Stack Pattern

Instead of storing values, store indices whenever distance or length is required.

Examples:

- Largest Rectangle in Histogram
- Sliding Window Maximum
- Longest Valid Parentheses

---

## Design Pattern

### LRU Cache

```text
HashMap
      +
Doubly Linked List
```

Time Complexity

- get() → O(1)
- put() → O(1)

---

### LFU Cache

```text
HashMap (Key → Node)

+

HashMap (Frequency → DLL)

+

Multiple Doubly Linked Lists
```

Time Complexity

- get() → O(1)
- put() → O(1)

---

# ⭐ Interview Formulas

### Histogram

```text
Width = NSE - PSE - 1
Area = Height × Width
```

---

### Contribution

```text
Contribution =
Element × Left Choices × Right Choices
```

---

### Stock Span

```text
Span =
Current Index - Previous Greater Index
```

---

### Trapping Rain Water

```text
Water =
min(LeftMax, RightMax) - Height
```

---

### Sliding Window Maximum

```text
Deque Front = Maximum Element
```

---

### Longest Valid Parentheses

```text
Length =
Current Index - Stack Top
```

Store **indices**, not characters.

---

# 📈 Time Complexity Summary

| Problem | Time | Space |
|---------|------|-------|
| Next Greater Element | O(N) | O(N) |
| Stock Span | O(N) | O(N) |
| Trapping Rain Water | O(N) | O(1) |
| Largest Rectangle | O(N) | O(N) |
| Maximal Rectangle | O(R × C) | O(C) |
| Sliding Window Maximum | O(N) | O(K) |
| Sum of Subarray Minimums | O(N) | O(N) |
| Asteroid Collision | O(N) | O(N) |
| Remove K Digits | O(N) | O(N) |
| LRU Cache | O(1) | O(Capacity) |
| LFU Cache | O(1) | O(Capacity) |

---

# 🚀 Key Takeaways

- Use **Monotonic Stack** for nearest greater/smaller element problems.
- Use **Contribution Technique** to avoid generating all subarrays.
- Convert **Binary Matrix → Histogram** for rectangle problems.
- Use **Deque** for Sliding Window Maximum.
- Store **indices instead of values** whenever distance or length is required.
- Use **HashMap + Doubly Linked List** for cache design problems.
- Always identify the underlying pattern before jumping into implementation.

